"":""2021-05-28T13:35:56Z""}}],""newsletters"":[{""name"":""Reuters Iran Briefing"",""promoBoxDescription"":""The Reuters Iran Briefing newsletter keeps you informed with the latest developments and analysis of the Iran war."",""landingPageUrl"":""/newsletters/reuters-iran-briefing/"",""sailThruId"":""reuters_iran_briefing""},{""name"":""Trading Day"",""promoBoxDescription"":""Make sense of global markets with the Trading Day newsletter."",""landingPageUrl"":""/newsletters/trading-day/"",""sailThruId"":""morning_bid_asia""},{""name"":""The Week in Breakingviews"",""promoBoxDescription"":""The Week in Breakingviews newsletter offers insights and ideas from Reuters' global financial commentary team."",""landingPageUrl"":""/newsletters/the-week-in-breakingviews/"",""sailThruId"":""week_in_BV""},{""name"":""Reuters Tariff Watch"",""promoBoxDescription"":""The Reuters Tariff Watch newsletter is your daily guide to the latest global trade and tariff news."",""landingPageUrl"":""/newsletters/reuters-tariff-watch/"",""sailThruId"":""tariff_watch""},{""name"":""Reuters Daily Briefing"",""promoBoxDescription"":""The Reuters Daily Briefing newsletter provides all the news you need to start your day."",""landingPageUrl"":""/newsletters/daily-briefing/"",""sailThruId"":""newsletter_subscription""}],""notification_settings"":{""title"":""World"",""braze_custom_attribute"":""application_world_alert""},""dart_zones"":{""topic"":""com,derv,ent,ivbk,econ,pol""},""excerpt"":{""content"":""Gold broke through $4,100 per ounce for the first time on Monday, hitting another record high on renewed U.S.-China trade tensions and expectations of U.S. interest rate cuts, while silver also rose to an all-time high."",""type"":""paragraph""},""content_elements"":[{""content"":""Gold broke through $4,100 per ounce for the first time on Monday, hitting another record high on renewed U.S.-China trade tensions and expectations of U.S. interest rate cuts, while silver also rose to an all-time high."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Spot gold was up 2.2% to $4,106.48 per ounce, as of 01:47 p.m. ET (1747 GMT), after hitting a record $4,116.77."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""U.S. gold futures for December settled 3.3% higher at $4,133."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Gold has climbed 56% this year and scaled the $4,000 milestone for the first time last week, driven by factors including geopolitical and economic uncertainties, expectations of U.S. interest rate cuts and robust central bank buying."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""\""Gold could easily continue its upward momentum. We could see prices north of $5,000 by the end of 2026,\"" said Phillip Streible, chief market strategist at Blue Line Futures."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Steady central bank purchases, firm ETF inflows, U.S.-China trade tensions and the prospect of lower U.S. interest rates are providing structural support for the market, Streible added."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""On the geopolitical front, U.S. President <a href=\""https://www.reuters.com/world/us/donald-trump/\"">Donald Trump</a> reignited trade tensions with <a href=\""https://www.reuters.com/world/china/trump-says-weighing-massive-increase-tariffs-chinese-imports-no-reason-meet-with-2025-10-10/\"">China</a> on Friday, ending an uneasy truce between the world's two largest economies."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Meanwhile, traders are pricing in a 97% probability of a 25-basis-point Federal Reserve rate cut in October and a 100% chance for December. Gold, a non-yielding asset, tends to do well in low-interest-rate environments.FEDWATCH/"",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Analysts at Bank of America and Societe Generale now expect gold to reach <a href=\""https://www.reuters.com/business/bofa-lifts-2026-gold-forecast-5000oz-sees-silver-65-2025-10-13/\"">$5,000</a> in 2026, while Standard Chartered has raised its forecast to an average of $4,488 next year."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""\""This rally has legs in our view, but a near-term correction would be healthier for a longer-term uptrend,\"" said Suki Cooper, global head, commodities research at Standard Chartered Bank."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Spot silver rose 3.1% to $51.82, touching a record high of $52.12 earlier in the session, buoyed by the same factors supporting gold and spot market tightness."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Technical indicators show both are overbought, with the relative strength index (RSI) at 80 for gold and 83 for silver."",""type"":""paragraph""},{""content"":""Platinum rose 3.9% to $1,648.25, and palladium gained 5.2% to $1,478.94."",""type"":""paragraph""}],""response_time"":1773171689968},""_id"":""b67102d95bf78b8b0f7e0710de807a7c70dc0166050a1d6876e24f1fb31047d5""};Fusion.globalContentConfig={""source"":""article-by-id-or-url-v1"",""query"":{""uri"":""/world/china/gold-hits-record-high-us-china-trade-woes-escalate-silver-scales-all-time-peak-2025-10-13/"",""website"":""reuters"",""published"":""true"",""website_url"":""/world/china/gold-hits-record-high-us-china-trade-woes-escalate-silver-scales-all-time-peak-2025-10-13/"",""arc-site"":""reuters""}};Fusion.lastModified=1773171690111;Fusion.contentCache={""site-hierarchy-by-name-v1"":{""{\""hierarchy_name\"":\""Website\"",\""website\"":\""reuters\""}"":{""data"":{""statusCode"":200,""message"":""Success"",""result"":{""id"":""/"",""website"":""reuters"",""name"":""Home"",""language"":""en"",""template_type"":""section"",""type"":""section"",""node_type"":""section"",""children"":[{""id"":""/world/"",""website"":""reuters"",""name"":""World"",""page_title"":""World"",""can_follow"":true,""language"":""en"",""template_type"":""section"",""type"":""section"",""advertising"":{""sponsored"":""true""},""node_type"":""section"",""children"":[{""id"":""/world/africa/"",""website"":""reuters"",""name"":""Africa"",""page_title"":""Africa"",""can_follow"":true,