nt during COVID 'paying off'"",""description"":""The healthcare sector has outpaced the S&P 500 so far this year, amid excitement around new drug development. Leah Bennett of Concurrent told Reuters drug companies raised over $50 billion of new investment in 2020, and they've used it since in developing mRNA technologies that were originally used for Covid vaccines, but which have since turned out to have crucial applications for cancer and other diseases.Â "",""published_time"":""2026-02-16T15:22:40Z"",""updated_time"":""2026-02-16T15:22:41Z"",""duration"":369.03,""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://ajo.prod.reuters.tv/api/v2/img/699334fbe4b08f93b605aee4""},""advert_info"":{""advert_params"":[{""key"":""adfriendly"",""value"":true}],""advert_zone"":""/4735792/reuters.com""},""source"":{""hls"":""https://ajo.prod.reuters.tv/v3/playlist/744535/master.m3u8""},""channels"":[{""id"":""6ffc0233e09c26943b265ef3abd575b2d872818b"",""name"":""Business"",""regions"":[""US""]},{""id"":""d23a680af92f21d9109a5f24e859f2fbe6253134"",""name"":""Health"",""regions"":[""US""]},{""id"":""d45538fb92ef02a065c15e16d3dd6a297c2ae7d7"",""name"":""Technology"",""regions"":[""US""]},{""id"":""sectors-upclose"",""name"":""Sectors UpClose"",""regions"":[""US""]}]},{""id"":""RW403209022026RP1"",""title"":""Sectors Up Close: AI gives bigger firms 'scale advantage'"",""description"":""U.S. consumer spending remains resilient, even as the job market looks weak, something many economists have put down to the so-called 'K-shaped' economy, or the gulf between higher and lower income Americans. Sarah Henry of Logan Capital Management told us the real winners of 2026 among retailers, though, will be the biggest names, like Walmart, who can afford to scale up AI tools to their advantage.Â "",""published_time"":""2026-02-09T15:47:31Z"",""updated_time"":""2026-02-09T15:47:32Z"",""duration"":318.1,""thumbnail"":{""url"":""https://ajo.prod.reuters.tv/api/v2/img/698a007ee4b0853002f8305b""},""advert_info"":{""adve